Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.68,0:00:04.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Waiting gets us nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.10,0:00:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a step forward into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.43,0:00:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a deduction and love countdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.97,0:00:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has another rival to Shin'ichi appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.14,0:00:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a contest to solve the paper plane puzzle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.85,0:00:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.94,0:00:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.53,0:01:59.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A new member of the Black Organization has been activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.47,0:02:04.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,An agent who is killed at intelligence gathering\Nas well as observation and discernment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.45,0:02:06.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Codename: Bourbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.80,0:02:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need to be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.10,0:02:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I solved the arson case over Sugiura\NKaito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s apartment building, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.18,0:02:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the residents of the apartment building who\Nlost his home in the fire, Okiya Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.35,0:02:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is now staying for free at my,\Nthat is to say, Kudo Shin'ichi's, house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.82,0:02:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran and Sonoko, who didn't know about it, mistook him for a burglar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.37,0:02:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder, is Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} all right after being kicked by Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.00,0:02:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recently a paper plane prankster has been annoying the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.83,0:02:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Night after night hundreds of paper planes\Nhave been scattered around the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.34,0:02:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those planes had been detailed with unusual markings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.72,0:02:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw one of the planes in an image\Nattached to an e-mail Ran sent me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.39,0:02:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realized that a serious message was hidden on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.10,0:02:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.76,0:03:09.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A different kind of paper airplane?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.35,0:03:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I remember from the news that close to 100 had been\Nrecovered in the city area yesterday morning and the before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.96,0:03:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, if the message drawn on the paper planes was\Ndifferent between yesterday and the day before...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I think might be able to narrow down the\Nlocation of the person who's sending this SOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.98,0:03:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, when was this found in the garden at your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.02,0:03:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it the morning of the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.85,0:03:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before that, won't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.35,0:03:38.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is that paper plane an SOS?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.69,0:03:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the pattern drawn on the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.36,0:03:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The size of the circles on the top and bottom are roughly the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.86,0:03:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the lengths of the three lines are three times width of the circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.44,0:03:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the distance from circle to circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.45,0:03:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is exactly the width of a single circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And thus, these are...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.08,0:04:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The symbols of Morse code, which is frequently\Nused as a means of communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morse code? That thing that's always in those old movies?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The circles are the short sounds, or dots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.55,0:04:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lines are the long sounds, or dashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Morse code, three dots are an "S".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three dashes are an "O".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.35,0:04:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.52,0:04:20.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An SOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.15,0:04:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"That means it's a signal from someone asking to be rescued."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he wrote in the e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.20,0:04:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} figured it out too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.33,0:04:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then he asked, if there was a different kind\Nof paper plane, for me to send him a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.83,0:04:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.54,0:04:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, the name of the owner\Nof this house was Shin'ichi too, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.25,0:04:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you don't know? He's a detective\Nwho's a high-school student, Shinâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.30,0:04:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.42,0:04:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K-Kinichi's this boy in my class who's a real mystery lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not "Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}", but "Kinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}" instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.64,0:05:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah. The Shin'ichi who's the owner of this house is just\Na regular high-school student with no special abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.10,0:05:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a regular high-school student?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.81,0:05:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not what I think at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.44,0:05:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.99,0:05:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason, even though I'm told he lived\Nhere, there's no trace of him left at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no clothes, or a diary, or even\Nanything like a photo album here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.83,0:05:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm just saying what I've noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.63,0:05:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he cleaned everything up because he'd be\Nembarrassed if we saw them when we came to clean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.46,0:05:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of cleaning things up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.42,0:05:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earlier, when we were at Welcome Burger...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.05,0:05:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the manager asking an employee to clean up\Nthe paper plane that had gotten caught in the sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.27,0:05:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry and get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.06,0:05:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait a sec! Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.44,0:05:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what was with that "Kinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}" stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.82,0:05:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, earlier Shin'ichi told me not to talk about him to that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:05:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.66,0:06:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he might take some strange interest and\Nhe didn't want him looking through his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan kun told me something like that in an e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.38,0:06:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, that's just like a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.59,0:06:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They love to investigate other people,\Nbut the reverse is "no good" eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.22,0:06:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.39,0:06:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.10,0:06:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something made me stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.60,0:06:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have an uneasy feeling that I shouldn't\Ntalk about Shin'ichi to that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.69,0:06:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So next, why don't you all try writing the\Nnames of the flowers in katakana?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.28,0:06:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Ran sure is slow...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.74,0:06:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be there was only that one kind of paper airplane?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.12,0:06:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She finally sent it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.62,0:06:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like yesterday's paper planes were different\Nfrom the ones the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.75,0:06:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll send you a picture, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.55,0:06:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no pattern on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.26,0:06:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I look closely though...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.63,0:07:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are five lines on the fold of the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.85,0:07:03.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Morse code, five dashes means zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.31,0:07:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what on earth could zero mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a pattern on the opposite side too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.65,0:07:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like the lines are just drawn alongside the folds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.07,0:07:19.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Could this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An antenna mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.24,0:07:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like on a cellphone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true! They're the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.04,0:07:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, if we add that together with\Nthe five dashes on the body, we get:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.84,0:07:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Zero radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.13,0:07:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, considering the initial SOS...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.55,0:07:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm being held captive in a location where\Nradio waves don't reach. Please rescue me."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.47,0:07:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what it would mean, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.10,0:07:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing! Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're a great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.02,0:07:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.23,0:07:53.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with this, as of yet all we know is\Nit's a place outside reception range.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A place outside reception range? Like a cave\Ndeep within the mountains or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.28,0:08:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the paper planes have only been found inside the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.20,0:08:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what about below ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.57,0:08:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would it be able to fly from below\Nground into the garden at your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.33,0:08:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.20,0:08:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.58,0:08:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were found yesterday and the day before, but what about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.67,0:08:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! The TV news!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.87,0:08:22.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The identity of the kidnapper who, whiles escaping, committed suicide\Nby leaping from a building early this morning has yet to be established.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.58,0:08:27.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The whereabouts of the kidnapped naval construction\Ncompany president, Daita Ikou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is also still unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.74,0:08:31.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The police are also considering following\Nup on any grudges against Daita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.51,0:08:35.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The kidnapper may have planned...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.60,0:08:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all that's on this channel too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.32,0:08:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man, President Daita, used his experience as a former sailor\Nto bring his company, with great effort, though lots of hardships.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.28,0:08:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what they said on the news this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.49,0:08:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could what be, Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.24,0:08:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This kidnapping case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.91,0:08:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might be related to the paper airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was kidnapped and is still being confined somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.34,0:09:02.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It makes sense that he could be throwing out these SOS\Npaper planes every night without the culprit seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.59,0:09:05.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this President Daita is the paper plane prankster?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.30,0:09:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a high probability.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he was a former sailor...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.48,0:09:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be strange for him to know Morse code, since they\Nuse it as a means of communication during emergencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.19,0:09:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, still not knowing that the kidnapper committed\Nsuicide, he's trying to get help without the culprit realizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.78,0:09:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. That way, even if the culprit happened to pick one\Nof these up, it would look to him like some kid's prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.87,0:09:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the paper planes found yesterday and the day before...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.71,0:09:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were made from single pages ripped out of a magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,President Daita's might be restricted from moving very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.59,0:09:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so he can't reach anything except that magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.59,0:09:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:49.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And now moving on, we're following up on\Nthe story of the paper plane prankster.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.10,0:09:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.35,0:09:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now I'm at the park near the Beika Tower Apartments where\None of the controversial paper planes was found this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.98,0:10:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, first of all, regarding the patterns on the plane this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.48,0:10:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't any on this side, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.57,0:10:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One the opposite side, there's one circle and four\Npartial circles drawn in a symmetrical pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.66,0:10:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, looking closely, there are also some strange creases.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.00,0:10:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This only serves to deepen the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.25,0:10:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Creases?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.87,0:10:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't see it very well on the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now, we're in the middle of class.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.68,0:10:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s working really hard making paper airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.48,0:10:39.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.06,0:10:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can do that during the break.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.90,0:10:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, teacher, but can you leave me alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.19,0:10:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now look here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.03,0:10:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's life is probably at stake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.03,0:10:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.37,0:10:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person releasing these things could possibly be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.70,0:10:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kidnapped President Daita.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he's being confined in a location\Nwhere there's no cellphone reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.87,0:11:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Considering the fact that he's made and released\Nsuch a large number of paper planes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.09,0:11:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly likely he's been abandoned there while still confined.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.43,0:11:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he's without food or drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.80,0:11:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll be in danger soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.76,0:11:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using the paper plane that was found this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should be able to narrow down his location further.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's with these?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.60,0:11:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with the four partial circles and the strange creases?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.11,0:11:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I assume this is also Morse code...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.40,0:11:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These half circles probably combine to make one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.07,0:11:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So four half circles make two full circles...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus there's the original full circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.70,0:11:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A full circle would be "E".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.20,0:11:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two would be "I".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.79,0:11:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In romaji, that would be "El" or... "IE"? (house)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.83,0:11:42.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What "house" could he be talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.09,0:11:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.88,0:11:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, speaking of paper planes,\Nthere are lots of ways to fold them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.89,0:11:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are, you know. Lots of kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.10,0:11:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like an cicada! Or like a swallow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.43,0:12:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are even ones that resemble animals you'd\Ndefinitely never think you'd see flying through the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.12,0:12:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.70,0:12:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.17,0:12:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.25,0:12:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that a paper plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.34,0:12:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sort of looks like a squid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.34,0:12:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if that's it, shouldn't you fold the head part one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.39,0:12:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, this is good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who's been throwing these wanted the\Npeople who find them to make a squid this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.44,0:12:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that person you're talking about is the paper\Nplane prankster who's causing all this commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if you spread this squid open once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.07,0:12:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn the paper over and make a paper airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.87,0:12:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.66,0:13:01.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks exactly the same as the paper plane\Nthat was collected today, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.46,0:13:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.96,0:13:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the strange creases and the partial\Nblack circles come from making a squid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.59,0:13:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the real message that's being sent\Nto the people who pick them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.47,0:13:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.55,0:13:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That paper plane guy, he's not just pulling some prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.59,0:13:17.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, the day before, and today...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each day seemed to have a different pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.89,0:13:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you see there has to be some kind of message?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who's doing it? And why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.44,0:13:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we want to know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.86,0:13:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll have to have Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} solve the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.32,0:13:35.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.07,0:13:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.16,0:13:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.33,0:13:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those three circles mean "be"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.37,0:13:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Morse code written in a Japanese way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A single circle is "he".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.92,0:13:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other two indicate a consonant marker, and if we join them up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.63,0:13:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:13:59.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where's the message in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.22,0:14:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you recognize this shape?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shape?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.89,0:14:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A squid?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.10,0:14:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, if we join the two of them together?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.91,0:14:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be... Ika...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.11,0:14:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.49,0:14:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Beika City.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.03,0:14:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha. It's a pun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.99,0:14:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, a code is sort of like a pun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.91,0:14:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if these are being thrown out by President Daita,\Nwho's been kidnapped and held captive...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.25,0:14:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then if the culprit picked one up, he might not guess the meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.54,0:14:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's OK that he used a pun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.25,0:14:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where could President Daita be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.63,0:14:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember right, the first paper plane said "SOS" and the next\None said "A location with no cellphone reception," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.72,0:14:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Putting all three together would be: "Rescue me from the location in\NBeika City that has no cellphone reception where I'm held captive."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.06,0:14:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a place like that in Beika City except underground?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A high-rise building.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.62,0:14:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.69,0:15:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The base station antennas for the cellphone network are targeted\Ntowards the ground, where the population density is high.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore it's difficult to connect from high places.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.45,0:15:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you can connect, as a consequence of the height,\Nyou pick up radio waves from several base stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You often get roaming mode, and eventually you go outside the range.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.80,0:15:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two high-rise buildings in Beika City.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.38,0:15:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a hotel, people are coming and going to make the bed\Nand such, so, it's difficult to confine someone there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.43,0:15:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.10,0:15:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place where President Daita is being held captive\Ncould possibly be the Beika Tower Apartments.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.48,0:15:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! That's really close by!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.90,0:15:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, the message about being out of range is\Nlikely only a hint about where he's being confined.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.23,0:15:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because in reality the culprit would probably have taken his cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.57,0:15:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, we should tell the police about this right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.12,0:15:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.29,0:15:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran! It's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.04,0:15:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.29,0:15:51.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm still at Shin'ichi's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.88,0:15:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's perfect. Can you head over to the\NBeika Tower Apartments near you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.05,0:16:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where the kidnapped President Daita is being confined!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you solved the paper plane code?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.69,0:16:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But I'll explain later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.39,0:16:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are some binoculars in the\Nsecond drawer of the desk in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.31,0:16:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take those and get on the observation elevator\Nat the New Beika Hotel for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ask Sonoko to call the police and get there as fast as you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I should have gone with Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.24,0:16:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's trust that she and he can handle things at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mystery lover, Kinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.17,0:16:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.06,0:16:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Shin'ichi, I can only see one side\Nof the apartment complex from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.39,0:16:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah if it's on the side you can't see then we're\Nwasting time, but there's nothing we can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.21,0:17:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.21,0:17:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's the apartment on the far end\Nof the east side on the 36th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.92,0:17:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The window is open a little and there's\Na pile of paper planes on the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.42,0:17:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, even if you've found the place where he's\Nconfined, don't try going in there on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.51,0:17:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The possibility is close to zero, but an accomplice\Nof the kidnapper might still be in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.35,0:17:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK. In that case, I'll inform Sonoko by e-mail\Nand she can take this all to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.02,0:17:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happened? Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.53,0:17:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.19,0:17:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A paper plane just flew by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.57,0:17:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's been made from a 10,000 yen bill!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.61,0:17:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.74,0:17:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing written on it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.16,0:17:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did President Daita send this too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.83,0:17:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.62,0:17:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with nothing written on it, if money comes raining down...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.16,0:17:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will get everyone excited and they'll search for where it's\Ncoming from, and it'll get reported to the police too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.17,0:17:59.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's his aim.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.38,0:18:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But him doing something like that during the day, taking on the risk\Nthat the culprit will notice, means it's come down to life-or-death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.97,0:18:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, that means President Daita's condition is really bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.01,0:18:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paper planes were initially found on\Nthe morning of the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's been nearly three days since he started throwing them out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.15,0:18:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, the culprit committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.40,0:18:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he's been left alone without being provided food and water...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that he's extremely dehydrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.03,0:18:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll call the police and an\Nambulance, so, Ran, you stay there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.95,0:18:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what would you do, Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.04,0:18:31.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.74,0:18:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't wait at a time like this, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.96,0:18:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.91,0:18:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'm going too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.75,0:18:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.71,0:18:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's still a chance that the culprit had an accomplice!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.34,0:18:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't you say the probability was almost zero?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.21,0:18:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was you, you'd rush into the room to help right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me how!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.18,0:18:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.02,0:18:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Yamakawa from the insurance company.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.23,0:18:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.61,0:19:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, coming. Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.62,0:19:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, I was just riding the elevator at the hotel and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.08,0:19:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a suspicious person on the veranda of this apartment!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.42,0:19:20.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please call the police right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.13,0:19:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.40,0:19:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.42,0:19:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a high-rise apartment complex, they are\Nrequired by law to install escape ladders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can reach him from the apartment just above.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.48,0:19:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.07,0:19:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the kidnapped man, President Daita, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.36,0:19:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw your paper airplanes and I've come to rescue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.24,0:19:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.33,0:19:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you find him, first lay him down on his side,\Nand don't forget to cushion his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:20:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then wet a handkerchief with lukewarm water and apply it to his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.08,0:20:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the best emergency treatment you can give him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.21,0:20:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-The ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.55,0:20:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has it been paid?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.51,0:20:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's all been taken care of, so don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.57,0:20:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! So there really was an accomplice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.26,0:20:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.82,0:20:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, leave the rest to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.57,0:20:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already heard the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.32,0:20:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're Mouri Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.95,0:20:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.91,0:20:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That high-school student who called, is he your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.16,0:20:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. Nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.08,0:20:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pass along something to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.33,0:20:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The situation was easy enough to understand in brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.33,0:20:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can understand him being impatient, but\Nthere's no point to just ranting on and on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.17,0:20:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he sure expressed his desperation well enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.76,0:20:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, it turned out that apartment belonged\Nto the culprit and there never was an accomplice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.69,0:21:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He committed the crime because he was pressed by debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.60,0:21:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,President Daita recovered from his confinement shortly thereafter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.19,0:21:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the uproar over the strange paper airplanes came to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.45,0:21:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} got all upset and started ranting?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.62,0:21:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the emergency personnel and to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.78,0:21:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Even after he was really calm when he was\Ndirecting me. That's not like Shin'ichi, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.37,0:21:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was because his beloved wife was in a crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.42,0:21:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be! That would be out of character for that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.32,0:21:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm not his wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.47,0:21:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, to be blunt, it could have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I honestly don't remember what I said then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.56,0:21:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My tension flared up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.60,0:21:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I only had a single thought in my head...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.52,0:21:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't let this tomboyish rescue squad member die.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.58,0:23:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, that deduction showdown\Nbetween Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Who won?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.62,0:23:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.71,0:23:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deduction showdown?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.17,0:23:35.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, President Daita's been rescued safely, so I wonder if\NSubaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is having a celebratory drink just about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.67,0:23:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A celebratory drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.22,0:23:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was on the shelf in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.63,0:23:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bottle of alcohol that wasn't there when I was cleaning before.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to have you tell my fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.24,0:24:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to know no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.08,0:24:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! A red-flanked blue tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.04,0:24:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.92,0:24:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door's locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.59,0:24:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means this was...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.43,0:24:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sealed room murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.78,0:24:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.67,0:24:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bluebird
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.86,0:24:52.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, where is my "bluebird of happiness"?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.25,0:24:53.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.47,0:24:54.48,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, there it goes.
